- Polymorphism (uses inheritance)
  ------------
"MANY FORMS!"
"The ability to look to an object in ..multiple ways!"
"Object with multiple shapes or forms..!"

E.g:
1) Overloading
2) Generics
3) Operators

class Animal				// Generalized form
class Dog extends Animal	// Specialized form

// Dog -> Animal

Dog dog = new Dog();
Animal animal = new Dog();	// Dog is both a Dog as well as an Animal!
Animal[] zoo = new Animal[100];

zoo[0] = new Tiger();
zoo[1] = new Dog()'
..

public void feed(Animal animal) {}
feed(dog);
feed(animal);



"Class Definition:
------------------
type:    aVar.getClass().getName();
parent:  aVar.getClass().getSuperClass();
methods: aVar.getClass().getMethods();

(aVar instanceof ObjType) // ObjType maybe a class or an interface